Class Descriptions:

ENGR010 - Introduction to Engineering
This introductory course explores the different engineering disciplines to assist students in a choice of a major in engineering.
Prospective engineering students have the opportunity to learn about experimentation, data analysis, problem-solving,
engineering software, basic computer programming, and the engineering design process.

PHYS004A - Engineering Physics - Mechanics
This is the first semester of a three-semester Physics sequence intended for students majoring in Physical Sciences and Engineering.
Mechanics is the first course in the Engineering Physics series. The course introduces students to concepts such as vectors,
kinematics, dynamics, energy, momentum, universal gravity, rotational physics, fluid dynamics, and elasticity.
